pull_request.title: fixing multiple defs linker errors
pull_request.body: We need those flag variables to be `extern` in the header file, otherwise we get "multiple definition error" when linking object files that each include "common.h" (that's why the liboqs-cpp wrapper is emitting a linker error in unit testing). Do we want the flags to be visible in the oqs object file? That's what I assumed, and used `OQS_API` for the definitions in `common.c`.

pull_request.title: Disable -Wtoo-strict-overflow
pull_request.body:
Otherwise you'll be forced to change code that is valid, where the compiler is doing optimisations based on the assumption undefined behaviour isn't happening, to code that is less clear (see  #693)

Closes #693

pull_request.title: fixing multiple defs linker errors
pull_request.body:
We need those flag variables to be declared `extern` in the header file `common.h`, and have them defined in `common.cpp`, otherwise we get "multiple definition error" when linking object files that each include "common.h" (that's why the liboqs-cpp wrapper is emitting a linker error in unit testing, see https://travis-ci.com/github/open-quantum-safe/liboqs-cpp/jobs/310866948). Do we want the flags to be visible in the oqs object file? That's what I assumed, and used `OQS_API` for the definitions in `common.c`.

We may also consider grouping all flags in a `struct`...

pull_request.title: Disable -Wtoo-strict-overflow
pull_request.body:
Otherwise you'll be forced to change code that is valid, where the compiler is doing optimisations based on the assumption undefined behaviour isn't happening, to code that is less clear (see  #693)

Closes #693

pull_request.title: add define indicating cpu_feature use
pull_request.body: `OQS_ENABLE_CPUFEATURES` if set indicates support for CPU feature (runtime) detection. Now only activated when `.CMake/cpu_extensions.cmake` executes OK. If not activated, eliminates the need for the `cpu_features` symbols/library. Resolves build issues when building without `Optimized` CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE set.
